cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on using video frames as input for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with audio input for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of sound. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition and lip reading. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks and attention mechanisms for speech recognition. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with both audio and video inputs for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
